  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To evaluate if the Ghost Ileostomy is really advantageous in laparoscopy we conducted a
      prospective randomized controlled study comparing 2 groups of patients undergoing anterior
      resection of the rectum laparoscopically. In the first group of patients at the end of the
      procedure was always performed a Ghost Ileostomy while in the second group no protective
      stoma was built at the end of the intervention.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
